File to Create: src/features/smc_signals.py
Pure indicator functions following same pattern as src/features/indicators.py. Input: full OHLCV DataFrame. Output: pd.Series per signal. No internal state, no lookahead (all backward-looking patterns).

1. Order Blocks (from OrderBlock.mq5 OB_MODE_DEFAULT)
Formula (translated from MQL5 to oldest→newest indexing):

Bullish OB at bar t (fired when break-up candle closes):
  c[t-2] < o[t-2]   # bar t-2 bearish
  c[t-1] < o[t-1]   # bar t-1 bearish
  c[t] > o[t]        # bar t bullish (confirmation)
  c[t-1] < low[t-2]  # t-1 closes below t-2's low
  c[t] > high[t-1]   # t breaks above t-1's high
  Zone = [high[t-1], low[t-1]]

Bearish OB at bar t:
  c[t-2] > o[t-2], c[t-1] > o[t-1], c[t] < o[t]
  c[t-1] > high[t-2], c[t] < low[t-1]
  Zone = [high[t-1], low[t-1]]
Output columns:

ob_bull: 1 if bullish OB formed at this bar, else 0
ob_bear: 1 if bearish OB formed at this bar, else 0
2. Fair Value Gaps (from OrderBlock.mq5 OB_MODE_FVG)
Formula:

Bullish FVG at bar t:
  c[t-3] < o[t-3], c[t-2] < o[t-2], c[t-1] > o[t-1]
  c[t-2] < low[t-3], c[t-1] > high[t-2], low[t] > high[t-2]
  Gap zone = [low[t-2], low[t]]  (unfilled price gap)

Bearish FVG at bar t:
  c[t-3] > o[t-3], c[t-2] > o[t-2], c[t-1] < o[t-1]
  c[t-2] > high[t-3], c[t-1] < low[t-2], high[t] < low[t-2]
  Gap zone = [high[t], high[t-2]]
Output columns:

fvg_bull: 1 if bullish FVG detected at this bar
fvg_bear: 1 if bearish FVG detected at this bar
fvg_size: size of the gap in pips (0 if no FVG)
3. Previous Day High/Low (from DailyHighLow.mq5)
# Resample to D1, shift 1 day (previous day), forward-fill to M15
daily = df["high"].resample("D").max().shift(1)  # prev day high
prev_high = daily.reindex(df.index, method="ffill")
prev_low  = df["low"].resample("D").min().shift(1).reindex(df.index, method="ffill")
prev_mid  = (prev_high + prev_low) / 2
Output columns:

prev_day_high_dist: (close - prev_day_high) / ATR (normalized distance, + = above)
prev_day_low_dist: (close - prev_day_low) / ATR
prev_day_pos: (close - prev_day_low) / (prev_day_high - prev_day_low) (0–1 position)
4. Andean Oscillator (from AndeanOscillator.mq5, length=50, signal=9)
alpha = 2.0 / (length + 1)
# Recursive (vectorized with cumsum trick or loop):
up1[i] = max(max(c[i], o[i]), up1[i-1] - (up1[i-1] - c[i]) * alpha)
up2[i] = max(max(c^2, o^2),   up2[i-1] - (up2[i-1] - c[i]^2) * alpha)
dn1[i] = min(min(c[i], o[i]), dn1[i-1] + (c[i] - dn1[i-1]) * alpha)
dn2[i] = min(min(c^2, o^2),   dn2[i-1] + (c[i]^2 - dn2[i-1]) * alpha)
bull[i] = sqrt(dn2[i] - dn1[i]^2)
bear[i] = sqrt(up2[i] - up1[i]^2)
signal[i] = EMA(max(bull, bear), signal_length)
Output columns:

andean_bull: bull momentum component
andean_bear: bear momentum component
andean_signal: EMA of max(bull, bear)
andean_diff: bull - bear (direction strength)
5. SuperTrend (from SuperTrend.mq5, period=10, multiplier=3)
middle = (high + low) / 2
upper = middle + multiplier * ATR(10)
lower = middle - multiplier * ATR(10)
# Trend: +1 if close > upper[prev], -1 if close < lower[prev], else carry prev
Output columns:

supertrend_dir: +1 or -1 (trend direction)
supertrend_dist: (close - active_band) / ATR (normalized distance from the active band)
6. Heiken Ashi Direction
ha_close = (open + high + low + close) / 4
ha_open[i] = (ha_open[i-1] + ha_close[i-1]) / 2  # recursive
ha_dir = sign(ha_close - ha_open)  # +1 bullish, -1 bearish
ha_body = abs(ha_close - ha_open) / ATR  # normalized body size
Output columns:

ha_dir: +1 or -1
ha_body_norm: body size normalized by ATR
Injection Architecture
CRITICAL DESIGN CHOICE: Add signals via extra_spec in the comparison script — NOT by modifying _DEFAULT_SPEC in feature_pipeline.py. This keeps the champion config untouched until signals are validated.

All 6 signal functions are OHLCV-based → must be added to _OHLCV_FUNS set in feature_pipeline.py line 72 when importing. Use this pattern in the comparison script:

from src.features.smc_signals import (
    order_block_bull, order_block_bear,
    fair_value_gap_bull, fair_value_gap_bear, fair_value_gap_size,
    prev_day_high_dist, prev_day_low_dist, prev_day_pos,
    andean_bull, andean_bear, andean_signal, andean_diff,
    supertrend_dir, supertrend_dist,
    ha_dir, ha_body_norm,
)

SMC_SPEC = [
    (("ob_bull", "ob_bear"), order_blocks, {}),
    (("fvg_bull", "fvg_bear", "fvg_size"), fair_value_gaps, {}),
    (("prev_day_high_dist", "prev_day_low_dist", "prev_day_pos"), prev_day_levels, {}),
]
ANDEAN_SPEC = [
    (("andean_bull", "andean_bear", "andean_signal", "andean_diff"), andean_oscillator, {"length": 50}),
]
TREND_SPEC = [
    (("supertrend_dir", "supertrend_dist"), supertrend, {"period": 10, "multiplier": 3.0}),
    (("ha_dir", "ha_body_norm"), heiken_ashi, {}),
]
The enc8 encoder takes raw 50-bar OHLCV windows, not the feature matrix — so adding features via extra_spec does NOT affect encoder behavior. Encoder stays frozen.

